[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man charged with attempted murder after Caerphilly attack

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been charged with the attempted murder of a 61-year-old in Caerphilly.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The man suffered serious injuries after being attacked on Cardiff Road on Thursday evening.
A 43-year-old man, who was arrested, has also been charged with possession of an offensive weapon and is due at Newport Magistrates' Court on Saturday.
The injured man remains in Cardiff's University Hospital of Wales in a stable condition.
